    "where Normalize(a) = a/∑ j a j.",
    "Together, these two steps ensure that the pseudo-labels are both accurate (by aligning with the ground truth distribution) and consistent (by forming a valid probability distribution), thereby improving the model's ability to learn from unlabeled data.",
    "Additionally, since ground truth labels typically adopt hard (1-hot) encoding, we further modify the calibrated pseudo-labels by applying a sharpening function:",
    "where T is a hyperparameter.",
    "As T approaches 0, the output will approach a one-hot distribution."
